White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki provided an update on the cyberattack on the Colonial Pipeline and the administration's response. Secretary of Transportation Pete Buttigieg and Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency Michael Regan also gave updates on their respective agencies' efforts to address the fuel supply disruptions caused by the cyberattack. They discussed measures being taken to alleviate potential shortages, including issuing waivers for certain fuel requirements, relaxing enforcement of pipeline operator qualification rules, and providing flexibility for truckers transporting fuel. Secretary Buttigieg emphasized the importance of resilient and secure infrastructure, including cybersecurity. The press conference also touched on other topics, such as the recent ousting of Representative Liz Cheney from her leadership position, the situation in Israel, and the administration's approach to compromise and negotiations with Republicans.